# exercise2 = Exercise.create(name: "Incline Bench Press", description: "The incline bench press is a variation of the bench press and an exercise used to build the muscles of the chest. The shoulders and triceps will be indirectly involved as well. Lie flat on an incline bench and set your hands just outside of shoulder width. Set your shoulder blades by pinching them together and driving them into the bench. Take a deep breath and allow your spotter to help you with the lift off in order to maintain tightness through your upper back.
# Let the weight settle and ensure your upper back remains tight after lift off.
# Inhale and allow the bar to descend slowly by unlocking the elbows. Lower the bar in a straight line to the base of the sternum (breastbone) and touch the chest. Push the bar back up in a straight line by pressing yourself into the bench, driving your feet into the floor for leg drive, and extending the elbows.
# Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.", image_url: "https://cdn.muscleandstrength.com/sites/default/files/incline-bench-press.jpg", video_url: "https://www.muscleandstrength.com/exercises/incline-bench-press.html")
# exercise3 = Exercise.create(name: "Dumbbell Fly", description: "The dumbbell fly utilizes a chest fly movement pattern to isolate the muscles fo the chest to better help the muscles grow and become stronger. Pick up the dumbbells off the floor using a neutral grip (palms facing in). Position the ends of the dumbbells in your hip crease, and sit down on the bench. To get into position, lay back and keep the weights close to your chest. Once you are in position, take a deep breath, then press the dumbbells to lockout at the top. Slightly retract your shoulder blades, unlock your elbows, and slowly lower the dumbbells laterally while maintaining the angle at your elbow. Once the dumbbells reach chest level, reverse the movement by squeezing your pecs together and bringing the dumbbells back to their starting position. Without allowing the dumbbells to touch, start the next repetition, and continue until the set is completed.", image_url: "https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/form-check-10-1554408283.png?crop=0.888888888888889xw:1xh;center,top", video_url: "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ul7j4OkNRq4")
# exercise4 = Exercise.create(name: "Shoulder Press", description: "The Shoulder Press is an upper body strength training movement, traditionally performed with dumbbells or a barbell. The weight is pressed vertically overhead", image_url: "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1497/9682/articles/1_71d97192-f77f-47fa-a059-87456a2c1fb1.jpg?v=1647872386", video_url: "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0JfYxMRsUCQ")
# exercise5 = Exercise.create(name: "Dumbbell Lateral Raise", description: "The side lateral raise is an effective shoulder-strengthening movement designed to isolate the lateral head of the deltoid muscle. Performed regularly, this can help you develop stronger, broader shoulders. All you need is a pair of light dumbbells and enough shoulder flexibility to abduct your arms (lifting the weights out and away from your body) until they form a T shape at your shoulders.", image_url: "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1497/9682/articles/1_22b6dc92-2f1d-49a0-be71-74631fbe3e55.jpg?v=1653913558", video_url: "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=geenhiHju-o")
# exercise6 = Exercise.create(name: "Reverse Pec Deck Fly", description: "This shoulder exercise targets your posterior delts and requires a pec dec machine. It's also the perfect chest, back and shoulder workout for building mass. Face the machine, and position the seat so that the handles are at shoulder level on either side. Next, hold the handles with your palms facing inward. Tighten your torso and extend your arms out to the side, pushing through all the way.
